							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/naomiday/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Naomi-Day-headshot-square-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/Naomi-Day-headshot-square-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Naomi Day" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/naomiday/">Naomi Day</a></h6>
										Naomi Day is a teaching artist and interdisciplinary storyteller working with Black speculative fiction and film photography. Her short fiction has appeared in <em>Uncanny Magazine, FIYAH Magazine, Black Warrior Review</em>, and more. She’s currently working on her first novel.																			</div>
